# Code Commenter

## Overview
Add clear, helpful inline comments that explain complex logic.

## Activation
Activates when user says "add comments", "explain this code", or "comment this".

## Instructions

1. Identify complex or non-obvious code sections
2. Add comments that explain:
   - WHY, not WHAT (code shows what)
   - Business logic reasoning
   - Edge cases handled
   - Algorithm explanations

3. Avoid:
   - Obvious comments
   - Redundant descriptions
   - Outdated information

## Examples

**Input:**
```javascript
const result = arr.reduce((acc, val, i) => {
  if (i % 2 === 0) acc.evens.push(val);
  else acc.odds.push(val);
  return acc;
}, { evens: [], odds: [] });
```

**Output:**
```javascript
// Partition array elements by their index position (even/odd indices)
// Used for alternating display in the UI grid layout
const result = arr.reduce((acc, val, i) => {
  if (i % 2 === 0) acc.evens.push(val);  // Even indices: left column
  else acc.odds.push(val);                // Odd indices: right column
  return acc;
}, { evens: [], odds: [] });
```
